{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2335,"text":"I'm an industrial designer,"},{"time":3691,"text":"which means I create all these cool things"},{"time":5752,"text":"from ideas that we surround ourselves\nwith, or in this case,"},{"time":8935,"text":"geeky people surround themselves\nwith, for the most part."},{"time":11665,"text":"I have absolutely no background\nin biology, chemistry or engineering,"},{"time":16067,"text":"so bear with me, because I'll be talking\nabout biomedical engineering today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20278,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21311,"text":"And please do stay here in the meantime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25507,"text":"Industrial design is about\nmaking lots of things identical."},{"time":29502,"text":"The downside about that is,\nthere's something impersonal"},{"time":32224,"text":"about lots of identical things,"},{"time":33788,"text":"because when you're trying\nto design one thing for one person"},{"time":36765,"text":"to solve one issue,"},{"time":38158,"text":"you can't really do that"},{"time":39463,"text":"when you're making things\naimed more to a demographic model"},{"time":42549,"text":"or to a marketing requirements document,"},{"time":45027,"text":"which is what we live by."},{"time":46455,"text":"So I got disheartened\nby the whole process in general,"},{"time":49708,"text":"and went to rethink it\nand redesign designing altogether,"},{"time":52965,"text":"went way back to my early, early\ndesign inspirations,"},{"time":55847,"text":"and back to about eight years old,\nand that got me to this guy."},{"time":60870,"text":"Anyone here from MIT knows him"},{"time":63229,"text":"or has a tattoo or poster\nof him somewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65285,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66322,"text":"Anyone else in the room, just for a hint,"},{"time":68571,"text":"he is the engineer of engineers\nor the designer of designers."},{"time":72066,"text":"He is the guy who made bionics\na household word"},{"time":75542,"text":"in the form of the polyester-clad\nSix Million Dollar Man"},{"time":78705,"text":"that I grew up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81165,"text":"The thing that came from\nthis pop culture show,"},{"time":83740,"text":"the real takeaway, was two main things:"},{"time":86061,"text":"if you're designing for the person,\nfor a real person,"},{"time":89259,"text":"you don't settle for the minimum\nfunctional requirements;"},{"time":92494,"text":"you see how far beyond that you can go,"},{"time":94414,"text":"where the rewards really are\nway out in the fringe"},{"time":96877,"text":"of how far past that document you can go."},{"time":99285,"text":"And if you can nail that,"},{"time":100917,"text":"you stand to improve\nthe quality of life for somebody"},{"time":103449,"text":"for every moment\nfor the rest of their life."},{"time":105670,"text":"I kind of distilled that down\ninto a design philosophy,"},{"time":109423,"text":"and infuse that\ninto the studio that I have now;"},{"time":112762,"text":"I'm trying to get everyone\nto think along these lines."},{"time":115790,"text":"It's not a profound philosophy,\nbut it works for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121599,"text":"We work with prosthetic limbs,"},{"time":123401,"text":"and the first thing you see\nabout prosthetic limbs"},{"time":126165,"text":"is that they are engineering brilliance."},{"time":129381,"text":"They can do amazing things;"},{"time":130820,"text":"they can return all kinds\nof functionality and performance"},{"time":134625,"text":"back to somebody's life."},{"time":135902,"text":"But from the vantage\nof an industrial designer,"},{"time":138317,"text":"they're not quite there."},{"time":139561,"text":"What we don't see is the sculpture\nor the beauty or the individual qualities"},{"time":143893,"text":"or the uniqueness or the elegance to them."},{"time":146477,"text":"They are brilliant, mechanical,\nutilitarian devices."},{"time":151345,"text":"And that's great, except\nfor a lot of people, that doesn't work."},{"time":154751,"text":"People come to our studio all the time,"},{"time":156770,"text":"and they have bubble wrap and duct tape,"},{"time":159726,"text":"trying to approximate their original form."},{"time":162124,"text":"Or they'll have a gym sock\nstuffed with other gym socks"},{"time":164762,"text":"to try to recreate\nthe shape that once was;"},{"time":167293,"text":"and that, to us, is not thriving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170154,"text":"The body, to us,\nis not a mechanical entity,"},{"time":173515,"text":"where mechanical-only solutions\ncan address them."},{"time":176083,"text":"It's our personal sculpture,\nour kinematic sculpture."},{"time":179310,"text":"It is our canvas;"},{"time":180500,"text":"it represents not just our physicality,"},{"time":182480,"text":"but also a lot of our personality as well."},{"time":184614,"text":"So when you're designing for the body,"},{"time":186569,"text":"maybe the thing isn't to design\nfor mass production,"},{"time":189072,"text":"but to design with the body in mind,"},{"time":191546,"text":"to really think about curves\ninstead of hard geometry,"},{"time":194149,"text":"or uniqueness instead of identical."},{"time":197082,"text":"The problem is, we're constrained\nby mass production,"},{"time":199891,"text":"which makes a million identical things"},{"time":201843,"text":"but can't make one unique,\nindividualized thing."},{"time":204272,"text":"So we scrapped that\nin the new design process,"},{"time":206925,"text":"and we start with the person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208643,"text":"This is a three-dimensional scanner,"},{"time":210676,"text":"and that's what happens\nwhen you scan somebody:"},{"time":212920,"text":"you get three-dimensional data\ninto your computer."},{"time":215459,"text":"You can take the sound-side limb there,\nthe surviving limb, mirror it over,"},{"time":220065,"text":"and from now on,"},{"time":221256,"text":"anything in the process\nwill recreate symmetry --"},{"time":223662,"text":"something as personal\nand as hard to achieve"},{"time":225759,"text":"as symmetry in the body."},{"time":227553,"text":"And you create a product\nthat, no matter what,"},{"time":230060,"text":"it's going to be as unique\nas their fingerprint."},{"time":232379,"text":"In fact, our process is incapable\nof creating two identical things."},{"time":235925,"text":"So we run it through\ncomputer modeling, 3D CAD."},{"time":239490,"text":"Here, we actually infuse a lot\nof the individual's taste and personality"},{"time":244463,"text":"into it, everywhere we can,"},{"time":246115,"text":"and we three-dimensionally\nprint the results."},{"time":248444,"text":"We call the resulting parts \"fairings,\""},{"time":250372,"text":"because they're named\nafter the panels on a motorcycle"},{"time":253383,"text":"that turn it from a mechanical thing\ninto a sculptural thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256717,"text":"We tried this on Chad."},{"time":260231,"text":"Chad is a competitive soccer player,"},{"time":262581,"text":"lost his leg eight years ago to cancer."},{"time":264509,"text":"You can imagine,\nit's really tricky to play soccer"},{"time":266985,"text":"when you have titanium pipe\nwhere there used to be a leg."},{"time":269955,"text":"The resulting parts recreated his shape"},{"time":274010,"text":"and deliberately had an aesthetic\nthat look like sporting gear."},{"time":277105,"text":"We wanted it to make it look like\nhe just pulled it out of the gym bag,"},{"time":280541,"text":"so it's fairly utilitarian in that regard."},{"time":282932,"text":"Two things happened."},{"time":284136,"text":"One, we expected: his sense\nof his body came back to him."},{"time":288462,"text":"He was suddenly able to control\nthe ball, to feel the ball,"},{"time":291336,"text":"because his body remembered\nthat original shape that he had had"},{"time":294387,"text":"up until eight years ago."},{"time":295637,"text":"The other thing, though,\nis that the other members of the team"},{"time":298749,"text":"stopped thinking of him\nas the amputee on the team."},{"time":301530,"text":"Not that they didn't know, but it stopped\nbecoming a focal point for him."},{"time":305090,"text":"And there is a certain\nvery quiet value in that,"},{"time":308319,"text":"we like to believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310537,"text":"James lost his leg in a motorcycle crash."},{"time":313179,"text":"And the motorcycle is still a big part\nof James's personality and style."},{"time":316910,"text":"Check out the tattoo on his forearm."},{"time":319771,"text":"We three-dimensionally printed that\ninto what would be his calf."},{"time":323665,"text":"He has his tattoo, he has his morphology"},{"time":326304,"text":"and he has the materials\nof his motorcycle."},{"time":328642,"text":"And the result is interesting in that\nyou can't really tell at first glance"},{"time":333361,"text":"where the motorcycle stops\nand where James starts."},{"time":335812,"text":"It's kind of a chimera hybrid\nbetween the two,"},{"time":339299,"text":"and James likes that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341289,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344082,"text":"So, we don't ever try to make something\nlook like it could be human."},{"time":348584,"text":"Our whole goal is to be\nunapologetically man-made,"},{"time":351498,"text":"to take what's already there, morphology,"},{"time":354215,"text":"and just make it really\ncool and beautiful,"},{"time":356327,"text":"something that somebody\ncan't wait to show the world,"},{"time":358860,"text":"because that changes their look."},{"time":360420,"text":"You don't look at him and say,\n\"He's an amputee with a prosthetic.\""},{"time":363709,"text":"You say, \"He's a guy\nwith something really cool going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366488,"text":"Deborah wanted her curves back,"},{"time":368208,"text":"but she also just wanted\nwhat came out of it to be really sexy,"},{"time":372278,"text":"which is great for us to hear."},{"time":374672,"text":"We created this lace pattern\nthat lends itself well to 3D printing."},{"time":378833,"text":"We created the first leg, I think,"},{"time":380792,"text":"where the lace defines\nthe contour of the leg,"},{"time":384509,"text":"instead of the leg\ngiving form to the lace."},{"time":387288,"text":"We switched things over."},{"time":389077,"text":"What I like about this shot\nis you can see daylight through it."},{"time":392132,"text":"So we're not trying to hide anything;"},{"time":393967,"text":"the load-bearing carbon component\nis totally visible."},{"time":396510,"text":"We're just giving it form\nand shape and contours"},{"time":400228,"text":"that were hers to begin with."},{"time":403152,"text":"We made her another leg\nthat matched her purse,"},{"time":405933,"text":"just because we could."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407233,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":411108,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416022,"text":"We made another one\nwhere we laser-tattooed the leather,"},{"time":419384,"text":"because how cool would it be"},{"time":420805,"text":"to be able to change your tattoos out\nfrom one minute to the next?"},{"time":423986,"text":"Love that."},{"time":425348,"text":"We try to capture as much\nof somebody's personality as we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428337,"text":"This is George.\nHis will be finished next week."},{"time":432137,"text":"This is the raw computer data\nthat we deal with."},{"time":435399,"text":"He's kind of a classic,\ntimeless-type personality,"},{"time":439002,"text":"so we did herringbone tweed,\nbut in polished nickel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441932,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":443244,"text":"And Uve was all too proud\nto show his tattoos,"},{"time":445688,"text":"so we are laser-tattooing those\ninto the leather."},{"time":449189,"text":"Part of it is, yes, we're showing off,\nbecause we can do this,"},{"time":452202,"text":"but the other part is this connects him\nto what will be a part of him."},{"time":455647,"text":"That is something really valuable;\nwe believe in that."},{"time":458303,"text":"Tattoos are especially exciting for us."},{"time":460284,"text":"What happens if you take the tattoo,"},{"time":462105,"text":"which is a combination\nof somebody's personal taste and choice,"},{"time":465316,"text":"and their morphology,"},{"time":466926,"text":"but now, let's say, you remove the person."},{"time":469353,"text":"You get a free-floating tattoo\ndefining their body."},{"time":473365,"text":"So everything we do is about recreating\nand expressing something"},{"time":477732,"text":"that means something to that person,"},{"time":479493,"text":"and expressing that through\nwhat would be their body,"},{"time":482063,"text":"whether it's speed or attitude or bling,"},{"time":485968,"text":"whatever it is that captures\nand suggests them in the best way we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491251,"text":"Back to the 3D-printing thing\nand this whole process:"},{"time":493795,"text":"we have a process that lends itself\nto making one thing per person;"},{"time":497146,"text":"it's very individual, and it actually\nreally lends itself well to complexity."},{"time":500982,"text":"So why not just print the entire leg?"},{"time":502955,"text":"That's the concept that preceded\nthe work we're doing now."},{"time":506871,"text":"This is a three-dimensionally printed leg.\nIt's symmetric to the other leg."},{"time":511071,"text":"It is made in America,"},{"time":513460,"text":"it is a trivially low-carbon footprint\nto create, curbside recyclable,"},{"time":519135,"text":"costs about 4,000 dollars to create,"},{"time":521920,"text":"and it is dishwasher-safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524201,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526109,"text":"There's a value to that, too."},{"time":527615,"text":"People don't think\nabout that all the time,"},{"time":529694,"text":"but yes, throw it in the dishwasher,\nit works just great."},{"time":532528,"text":"This was based on the original idea\nthat I could go anywhere in the world"},{"time":536064,"text":"with nothing more than a camera\nand a laptop computer,"},{"time":538701,"text":"use the camera as a 3D scanner and create\nfor somebody, in a matter of hours,"},{"time":542504,"text":"a very high-quality, three-dimensionally\nprinted leg for a very low cost."},{"time":546186,"text":"The proof of concept works great,\nwe're finding it; we'll get there."},{"time":550699,"text":"Or, we upped the quality of the materials\nand created this for John."},{"time":554556,"text":"The fun thing with John's leg\nis that when his fiancee looked at this,"},{"time":559074,"text":"she joked and said, \"I like that leg\nbetter than that leg.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":562997,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":564694,"text":"And it's a joke -- she knows full well\nwhat he goes through --"},{"time":568039,"text":"but at the same time,\nthere's something very valuable."},{"time":570671,"text":"He turned to us and said,\n\"Nobody says that.\""},{"time":572902,"text":"He's never heard that in his life."},{"time":574594,"text":"That connected with him very deeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577301,"text":"So we like to think\nthat this is a new type of design,"},{"time":580619,"text":"where you're turning\nthe original process on its head,"},{"time":584829,"text":"where there is a dialogue that forms\nbetween the designer and the end user,"},{"time":588397,"text":"where the designer relinquishes\nsome of the control --"},{"time":591012,"text":"designers hate doing that --"},{"time":592376,"text":"and instead, is the curator of a process."},{"time":595773,"text":"And the end user relinquishes their body\ninto the process, and their taste."},{"time":600070,"text":"I'd like to think that speaks\nto a greater change that's happening"},{"time":603378,"text":"in the design world altogether;"},{"time":604962,"text":"in this case, it's one where\nproducts will be evaluated"},{"time":608613,"text":"on how well they address the individual."},{"time":612264,"text":"The individual will actually be\npart of the DNA of the end product itself."},{"time":617310,"text":"We will be evaluating products\non how well they address a unique person,"},{"time":621706,"text":"instead of a demographic model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624316,"text":"This all really hit home for us\nin one of the first legs we did;"},{"time":628141,"text":"when Chad here put on the leg,"},{"time":630882,"text":"reached down and felt it"},{"time":632566,"text":"and thought about it for a while."},{"time":634181,"text":"Then he turned to us and said,"},{"time":635786,"text":"\"That's the first time I've felt\nthat shape in eight years.\""},{"time":639783,"text":"We thought about that."},{"time":641223,"text":"And for all the technology"},{"time":642509,"text":"and all the nights\nand energy we put into it,"},{"time":645203,"text":"that's all we really wanted to hear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647769,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648985,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}